### Get reverse geocode
# Converts lat/lng coordinates to a street address.
# Requires reCAPTCHA token for unauthenticated access.
# Authenticated variant: GET /v1/reverse-geocode/authed (Cognito JWT, no reCAPTCHA required)

GET https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/reverse-geocode?latitude=38.897957&longitude=-77.03656 HTTP/1.1
x-recaptcha-token: {{choosee-api-recaptcha-token}}

# Response 200:
# { "address": "1600 Pennsylvania Avenue NW, Washington, DC 20500, USA" }
#
# Response 400: missing/invalid latitude or longitude
# Response 403: reCAPTCHA score too low
# Response 404: no address found for the given coordinates

###

### Create session
# Starts a new restaurant-picking session. Returns immediately with a sessionId;
# the actual Google Places lookup runs asynchronously in a separate Lambda.
# Poll GET /sessions/{sessionId} until isReady=true or errorMessage is set.
#
# radiusMiles: search radius in miles (min/max from GET /sessions/config)
# rankBy: "POPULARITY" | "DISTANCE" | "ALL" (from GET /sessions/config sortOptions)
# type: array of place type values (from GET /sessions/config placeTypes)
# exclude: optional array of place type values to exclude
# filterClosingSoon: required boolean. When true, filters out restaurants that are
#   closed or closing within the next hour. Best-effort: places without structured
#   hours data are kept if Google reports them as open.
# maxChoices: optional integer. Caps the number of restaurants in the bracket.
#   For rankBy "ALL", results are interleaved (alternating popularity/distance)
#   before the cap is applied, so the extra slot goes to a randomly chosen list.
#   Omit to include all results returned by Google (up to 20).
# latitude/longitude: optional — both or neither. If omitted, address is geocoded.
#
# Authenticated variant: POST /v1/sessions/authed (Cognito JWT)

POST https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-recaptcha-token: {{choosee-api-recaptcha-token}}

{
  "address": "Columbia, MO 65203, USA",
  "type": ["restaurant"],
  "exclude": ["breakfast_restaurant"],
  "radiusMiles": 2.33,
  "rankBy": "POPULARITY",
  "filterClosingSoon": true,
  "maxChoices": 8
}

# Response 202:
# { "sessionId": "fuzzy-penguin" }
#
# Response 400: missing address, empty type array, invalid radiusMiles/rankBy,
#   missing or non-boolean filterClosingSoon
# Response 403: reCAPTCHA score too low

###

### Get session by ID
# Returns the current state of a session. Poll this after creating a session
# until isReady=true (success) or errorMessage is non-null (failure).

GET https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin HTTP/1.1

# Response 200:
# {
#   "sessionId": "fuzzy-penguin",
#   "address": "Columbia, MO 65203, USA",
#   "location": { "latitude": 38.9517, "longitude": -92.3341 },
#   "currentRound": 0,
#   "bracket": [[["choice-a", "choice-b"], ["choice-c", "choice-d"]]],
#   "byes": [null],
#   "isReady": true,
#   "errorMessage": null,
#   "users": ["brave-tiger"],
#   "winner": null,
#   "expiration": 1712448000,
#   "type": ["restaurant"],
#   "exclude": ["breakfast_restaurant"],
#   "radius": 3750,
#   "rankBy": "POPULARITY",
#   "filterClosingSoon": true,
#   "totalRounds": 2
# }
#
# Note: radius is stored in meters internally.
# While session is loading (isReady=false), response also includes:
#   "timeoutAt": 1712361600000  (ms timestamp — omitted once session is ready)
# totalRounds is 0 until the async Lambda sets it.
#
# Response 404: session not found or expired

