### Create user (join session)
# No request body required. Creates a new user in the session.
# If a Cognito JWT is present (via the /auth variant), the user's name, phone,
# and Google sub are extracted from the token claims.

POST https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/users HTTP/1.1

# Authenticated variant (requires Cognito JWT):
# POST https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/users/authed
#
# Response 201:
# {
#   "userId": "brave-tiger",
#   "name": "Alice",          (from JWT name claim, or null if unauthed)
#   "phone": "+15551234567",   (from JWT phone_number claim if valid US number, or null)
#   "subscribedRounds": [],
#   "votes": [[]],
#   "textsSent": 0,
#   "expiration": 1712448000
# }
#
# Response 400: max users reached (message includes limit)
# Response 404: session not found or expired

###

### Update user (name, phone, or vote)
# JSON Patch format. Allowed ops: replace, add, test.
# Allowed paths: /name, /phone, /votes/{round}/{matchupIndex}
#
# If all users have voted all matchups, the round closes automatically.
# If a Cognito JWT is present (via the /auth variant), the user's name and
# Google sub are backfilled from the token when still null.
#
# Authenticated variant (requires Cognito JWT):
# PATCH https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/users/brave-tiger/authed

PATCH https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/users/brave-tiger HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

[
  { "op": "replace", "path": "/name", "value": "Alice" }
]

# Example: set phone
# [{ "op": "replace", "path": "/phone", "value": "+15551234567" }]
#
# Example: submit vote for round 0, matchup 0
# [{ "op": "replace", "path": "/votes/0/0", "value": "choice-a" }]
#
# Response 200: updated user object
# Response 400: disallowed path, name > 50 chars, invalid phone, vote choice not in matchup
# Response 404: session or user not found
# Response 409: concurrent round advance conflict

###

### Close round
# Advances the bracket to the next round or determines a winner.
# roundId is a path parameter.

POST https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/rounds/0/close HTTP/1.1

# Response 200 (new round generated):
# { "sessionId": "fuzzy-penguin", "currentRound": 1, "bracket": [...], "winner": null, ... }
#
# Response 200 (winner determined):
# { "sessionId": "fuzzy-penguin", "currentRound": 1, "winner": "choice-a", ... }
#
# Response 200 (idempotent — roundId < currentRound): returns current session state
#
# Response 400: roundId does not match currentRound, session not ready
# Response 404: session not found or expired
# Response 409: concurrent round close (condition expression failure)

###

### Subscribe to round notifications
# Subscribes a user to receive an SMS when a new round starts.
# User must have a phone number set first.

POST https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/rounds/1/subscribe HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
  "userId": "brave-tiger",
  "roundId": 1
}

# Response 200: updated user object (subscribedRounds includes the new round)
#
# Response 400: user has no phone number set, invalid roundId
# Response 404: session or user not found

###

### Share session via SMS
# Creates a new user with the recipient's phone and sends an SMS with a join link.
# Requires Cognito JWT. The caller's Google sub must match the sharing user's sub.
# Path includes the sharing user's ID for rate-limit tracking and ownership verification.

POST https://{{choosee-api-host}}/v1/sessions/fuzzy-penguin/users/brave-tiger/share HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{cognito-jwt}}

{
  "phone": "+15559876543",
  "type": "text"
}

# Response 201:
# { "userId": "clever-fox" }
#
# Response 400: invalid phone format, max users reached
# Response 401: missing or invalid JWT
# Response 403: caller's Google sub doesn't match sharing user, or user not linked
# Response 404: session not found, sharing user not found, or expired
# Response 422: phone number already in use in this session
# Response 429: SMS rate limit exceeded (5 texts per user)
# Response 500: SMS send failed (userId of created user included in error body)
